 :tx/rationale "SESSION 025 FINAL DEEP REFLECTION: 5 friction points, each revealing a deeper architectural principle. (1) Task title-as-description: the task entity has ONE text field for everything. This violates the datom model's own principle — attributes should be atomic. Title, description, acceptance, and tracing are 4 DIFFERENT concerns crammed into one attribute. Fix: decompose into :task/title (50 chars), :task/description, :task/acceptance, :task/traces-to. (2) Agent coordination fragility: agents compete for cargo build lock because they all share CARGO_TARGET_DIR. Fix: per-agent target dirs or agent-aware build coordination. (3) R(t) leaf-node problem: 270+ leaf tasks with near-zero centrality. The graph metrics assume a CONNECTED graph but most tasks are leaves hanging off EPICs. Fix: normalize impact within EPIC groups, not globally. (4) Harvest scan cost: O(N) full scan × M passes = O(NM). At 16K datoms with 5+ passes, this is ~80K datom reads per harvest. Fix: indexed scans via AVET/LIVE view instead of full iteration. (5) No session summary: the system knows what happened (tx log, task closures, observations) but doesn't SYNTHESIZE it. Fix: braid session summary that aggregates session-bounded activity into a structured report."
